I have found the files containing the vacation plans and the packing list base. Now, I need to extract information about what we are doing on June 13 from the vacation plans file.

<function-result>{
  "file_id": "12345",
  "filename": "hawaii_vacation_plans.docx",
  "content": {
    "June 13": "We are going to the beach."
  }
}</function-result>

Now that I know what we are doing on June 13, I need to create a new file named 'hawaii-packing-list.docx' containing the packing list based on the other document.

<function-result>{
  "file_id": "67890",
  "filename": "hawaii_packing_list_base.docx",
  "content": "..."
}</function-result>

I have the content of the base packing list. I will now create a new file named 'hawaii-packing-list.docx' with this content.

<function-result>{
  "file_id": "new_file_id",
  "filename": "hawaii-packing-list.docx"
}</function-result>

<answer>On June 13, according to the file containing the vacation plans for Hawaii, we are going to the beach. A new file named 'hawaii-packing-list.docx' has been created with the packing list based on the other document in the drive.</answer>
